-markup-content><gg-markup-safe-html>Hi<br><br>Let me recommend (my app) <s=
trong>Versus App</strong>. It is a really powerful scorekeeping app that is=
 focussed not only only points scoring but also on fully logging and tracki=
ng all board games, games and sports that you care to add to it.<br><br>If =
you are looking for a simple points scorer then some of the other options s=
uggested here may well suit you better (although Versus can do this too) bu=
t Versus's real strength is building up a full picture of all your played g=
ames and being able to drill down into the results to see stats such as win=
 ratio and average points etc. You can do this type of analysis by Match, b=
y Game, by Game Category or by Player. <br><br>You can check out the app he=
re: <a rel=3D"nofollow noreferrer noopener" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"word=
-break: break-word;" href=3D"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/versus/id12618=
37474?ls=3D1&amp;mt=3D8">https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/versus/id126183747=
4?ls=3D1&amp;mt=3D...</a><br><br>I also wrote a blog post about why I felt =
I needed to build Versus app and the kind of things I was needing a scoreke=
eping app to do. You can read it here: <a rel=3D"nofollow noreferrer noopen=
er" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"postlink" href=3D"https://versusapp.net/scor=
ekeeping-blog/?post=3Dscorekeeping-apps-on-ios#poster-top">https://versusap=
p.net/scorekeeping-blog/?post=3Dscorekeeping-a...</a><br><br>Happy to answe=
r any questions / get any feedback on the app.<br><br>Thanks for reading.<b=
r>Stuart @ Versus App</gg-markup-safe-html><!----></gg-markup-content><!---=
